                            <comment id="122234" author="bzzz" created="Mon, 27 Jul 2015 05:19:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;in lfsck_create_lpf():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	char			  name&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;8&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
..&lt;br/&gt;
	rc = lfsck_lock(env, lfsck, parent, name, llh,&lt;br/&gt;
			MDS_INODELOCK_UPDATE, LCK_PW);&lt;br/&gt;
	if (rc != 0)&lt;br/&gt;
		RETURN(rc);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	snprintf(name, 8, &quot;MDT%04x&quot;, node);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so, LFSCK requests a lock with non-initialized name. it&apos;s strange that gcc doesn&apos;t complain..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
